snippet: In rejecting the online marketplace, Gov. Chris Christie of New Jersey cited a pending Supreme Court challenge to the Affordable Care Act, but his move was largely symbolic.
abstract: Gov Chris Christie of New Jersey vetoes an online marketplace created by the Legislature to help residents and small businesses buy health insurance, in a swipe at President Obama's signature health care legislation; cites a pending Supreme Court challenge to the Affordable Care Act, which requires most Americans to have health insurance and mandates states to have benefit exchanges.
lead_paragraph: In rejecting the online marketplace, Gov. Chris Christie of New Jersey cited a pending Supreme Court challenge to the Affordable Care Act, but his move was largely symbolic.

headline.seo: Christie Vetoes Health Insurance Exchange for New Jersey
headline.print_headline: Christie Vetoes Insurance Exchange, Citing Supreme Court Case on Health Care Law
